headline: Intel, Qualcomm, Tesla: 3 Stocks in Focus
summary: Intel (INTC) has secured more than $7.9 billion in federal funding from the Biden administration's CHIPS Act. Qualcomm (QCOM) is reportedly less interested in pursuing an acquisition of Intel, according to a Bloomberg report. Tesla (TSLA) could be excluded from California Governor Gavin Newsom's proposed electric vehicle (EV) rebates, which the governor said will take effect if President-elect Donald Trump kills federal EV tax credits. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.

headline: New Trump tariffs, Fed minutes, Intel CHIPS grant: 3 Things
summary: President-elect Donald Trump has threatened to levy import tariffs against China, Mexico, and Canada. Stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) appear mixed this morning on the headline, while shares Big Three automakers Ford (F), Stellantis (STLA), and General Motors (GM) move into negative territory in pre-market trading. Wall Street will be listening for the Federal Reserve to release the minutes from its November FOMC meeting, looking for any hints into the central bank's sentiments around its interest rate path ahead of its December meeting. According to Bloomberg, Intel (INTC) is set to receive $7.9 billion in CHIPS Act grants from the US government, while the chipmaker's interest in acquiring Qualcomm (QCOM) has cooled. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: Qualcomm's interest in acquiring Intel has cooled, Bloomberg News reports
summary: The complexities associated with acquiring all of Intel has made a deal less attractive to Qualcomm, Bloomberg reported, saying that it is possible Qualcomm may look at pieces of Intel instead or rekindle its interest later.  The companies did not respond to a request for comment on the Bloomberg report outside regular business hours in the U.S.
